This paper deals with visual navigation, which involves computer vision and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper proposes a fusion scheme for visual representations, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely sub-category. The paper also deals with navigation, which involves robotics, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible sub-category. The paper also proposes a data-driven approach, which involves machine learning and statistical techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques to identify objects, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) a possible sub-category.
